# Common Mistakes

## 1. Mixing Rows and Columns

Wrong

```java
for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++){

    for(int j = 1; j <= n; j++){

    }

}
```

When the pattern requires

```
j <= i
```

---

## 2. Forgetting `System.out.println()`

Without

```java
System.out.println();
```

everything prints on one line.

---

## 3. Incorrect Loop Bounds

Wrong

```java
j < i
```

instead of

```java
j <= i
```

One symbol will be missing in every row.

---

## 4. Ignoring Spaces

For pyramid patterns, spaces are as important as stars.

