# Competitive Programming Tips

- Pattern problems are mainly for building logic rather than appearing directly in contests.
- Always solve patterns by identifying **rows**, **columns**, and **relationships**.
- Dry-run your loops on paper before coding.
- Learn the general templates instead of memorizing every pattern.
- Pattern-solving skills improve your understanding of matrices, nested loops, and simulations.

